(1389, 184, 'content_biography', 'Personal trainer, of Colombian nationality, passionate about helping people improve their health. \r\nPassion that began with my first studies of nutrition in the Complutense University of Madrid.\r\nFrom a very young age I have travelled through different countries in which I have been able to meet wonderful people, as well as reinforce my knowledge in nutrition and personal training, discovering in this trajectory that my passion to help improve the lives of others is my number one goal, For which I have dedicated myself completely.\r\n\r\nI am Certified as a Personal Trainer at (Brookfield College Dallas TX), Specialized in Kettlebell Techniques at (S.E.C.A) and Spinning Instructor at (Mad Dogg Athletic)\r\n\r\nI am the founder and CEO of ANGELICA''S FITNESS AND NUTRITION CENTER and I am ready to help you improve your health.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nOur Philosophy\r\n\r\nIn our health and fitness center, we believe in changing lives through physical and nutritional education.\r\nThe physiological theory behind angelica training is nutrition along with a nutrition plan that maximizes your training experience. With more than 20th years of experience, we put our greatest effort on the needs of the customer, and what to do to improve your overall experience. That''s what makes our fitness center apart from the rest of the gyms.\r\n\r\nWe offer you an experience that will completely change your lifestyle to a better and healthier one.\r\n\r\n“Fitness is not a destination it is a way of life.”\r\n'),
